description.narrative: Output 2.1. Healthcare professionals have the capacity to provide quality perinatal, modern home visiting and adolescent-friendly services to the most disadvantaged boys and girls, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Sanitation, Water, Water (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, disadvantaged children have equitable access to health and education services to survive, learn, develop and contribute to resilient, inclusive and sustainable communities

description.narrative: In 2019, at least 10,000 newborns and children benefited from UNICEF assisted life-saving interventions due to the increased capacity of 125 healthcare providers and resuscitation equipment in 23 healthcare facilities. Another investment in water supply, sanitation and heating system of 11 healthcare facilities of the Southern Regions is expected to serve about 25,600 deliveries per year (17 percent of all deliveries in the country). Thousands of children will also have access to safer vaccines with newly installed 632 specialized refrigerators in vaccination points throughout the country. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/12/2019
